        <!-- Detailed Performance Section -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">In-Depth Performance</h2>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Computational Photography Excellence</h3>
                <p>
                    The OM-1 II's true strength lies in computational features.
                    High-Res Shot mode captures 50MP images by shifting the
                    sensor and combining multiple exposures‚Äîremarkably, this
                    works handheld with sufficient stabilization. The results
                    rival dedicated high-resolution cameras for static subjects,
                    perfect for landscape and architecture photography.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Live ND is transformative for video and long-exposure
                    photography. By using computational techniques, the camera
                    simulates ND2 through ND64 filters without physical glass.
                    This enables silky water motion, light trails, and motion
                    blur effects without carrying bulky filters. Starry Sky AF
                    automatically focuses on stars for astrophotography‚Äîa
                    feature unmatched by any competing system.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Speed & Autofocus</h3>
                <p>
                    The OM-1 II's 120 fps burst with full AF/AE tracking is
                    astonishing. While utilizing electronic shutter (with
                    attendant rolling shutter), it captures decisive moments
                    impossible with slower cameras. Pro Capture mode buffers up
                    to 70 frames before shutter release, ensuring you never miss
                    the peak action‚Äîinvaluable for wildlife and sports.
                </p>
                <p>
                    AF performance has improved notably. The 1,053-point
                    cross-type system with AI subject detection reliably tracks
                    birds, animals, motorcycles, cars, and trains. In good
                    light, it rivals full-frame cameras for subject acquisition
                    and tracking. Low-light AF (-8 EV) works adequately, though
                    not as confidently as larger-sensor competitors.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
                <p>
                    Video features are professional-grade. C4K (Cinema 4K) at
                    60p with 10-bit 4:2:2 provides excellent quality and color
                    latitude. OM-Log400 captures approximately 12+ stops of
                    dynamic range. The Live ND feature is particularly valuable
                    for video‚Äîenabling proper exposure in bright conditions
                    without expensive variable ND filters.
                </p>
                <p>
                    FHD 240fps provides high-quality slow motion for creative
                    work. The combination of excellent IBIS and digital IS
                    enables smooth handheld footage even with non-stabilized
                    lenses. Heat management is excellent‚Äî the camera can record
                    continuously without overheating concerns, crucial for
                    documentary and event work.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Build Quality & Weather Sealing</h3>
                <p>
                    The OM-1 II's build quality is exceptional. IP53 rating
                    means genuine protection against dust and water (not just
                    splash resistance). The magnesium alloy body is freeze-proof
                    to -10¬∞C, enabling shooting in conditions where other
                    cameras fail. Combined with weather-sealed Pro lenses, the
                    system is bombproof.
                </p>
                <p>
                    At 511g (body only), it's remarkably portable. With a
                    compact zoom like the 12-40mm f/2.8 PRO, the entire kit
                    weighs less than many full-frame bodies alone. This size
                    advantage enables all-day shooting without fatigue, crucial
                    for hiking, travel, and event coverage. Battery life is
                    excellent‚Äîapproximately 520 shots CIPA, often exceeding 800
                    in real-world use.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

